subject: Baseball
Little League
Little League World Series
lead_paragraph: Tanner Tokunaga hit a two-run double with the bases loaded and two outs to cap a six-run sixth inning for Waipahu, Hawaii, in its come-from-behind 7-5 victory over Lake Charles, La. Hawaii earned a spot in the Little League World Series title game Sunday in South Williamsport, Pa. It will play Matamoros, Mexico, which defeated Tokyo, 5-4.
